Jodhpur is a city located in the Thar Desert of Rajasthan, India.
It was founded by Rao Jodha of Mandore in 1459.
Also known as the Sun City, it is the second largest city in Rajasthan.
It is also known as the Gateway to Thar.
Mehrangarh Fort, the largest fort in India is located in Jodhpur.
Umaid Bhawan Palace is located in Jodhpur.


